      <title>🍑 How to Build Your Blog using Hugo</title>
      <link>https://yukatuan.github.io/post/%E5%A6%82%E4%BD%95%E4%BD%BF%E7%94%A8hugo%E6%90%AD%E5%BB%BA%E5%B1%AC%E6%96%BC%E8%87%AA%E5%B7%B1%E7%9A%84%E5%8D%9A%E5%AE%A2/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 May 2022 14:05:32 +0800</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://yukatuan.github.io/post/%E5%A6%82%E4%BD%95%E4%BD%BF%E7%94%A8hugo%E6%90%AD%E5%BB%BA%E5%B1%AC%E6%96%BC%E8%87%AA%E5%B7%B1%E7%9A%84%E5%8D%9A%E5%AE%A2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hugo is written by Go Language and can help us build a beautiful blog in a very short time。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-hugo&#34; &gt;Install Hugo
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#install-hugo&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;mac&#34; &gt;MAC
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#mac&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;brew install hugo
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo version
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;win&#34; &gt;WIN
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#win&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download corresponding &lt;code&gt;.zip&lt;/code&gt; document in the  &lt;code&gt;hugo release&lt;/code&gt; page&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;unzip &lt;code&gt;hugo.exe&lt;/code&gt; file and put it into &lt;code&gt;D:\Software\hugo&lt;/code&gt;(You can choose your own path)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;add the above into &lt;code&gt;path&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Right click &lt;code&gt;my computer&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attributes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced system settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;environment variables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;double click path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;new path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Restart the terminal, run &lt;code&gt;hugo version&lt;/code&gt;. The version number indicates success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;build-a-blog&#34; &gt;Build a Blog
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#build-a-blog&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Enter hugo official website（&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/getting-started/quick-start/&#34;&gt;https://gohugo.io/getting-started/quick-start/&lt;/a&gt;）, follow the steps to build it step by step.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notice&lt;/strong&gt;：&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;hugo new site quickstart
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;quickstart&lt;/code&gt; need to be changed into your github repository name and add &lt;code&gt;-generator&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;create-a-new-terminal&#34; &gt;Create a New Terminal
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#create-a-new-terminal&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run hugo in the terminal (generate the public folder); you can also use &lt;code&gt;hugo -F --cleanDestinationDir &lt;/code&gt;(generate a new folder)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a new .gitignore on the outermost side and enter:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;/public/&lt;/code&gt; &lt;br&gt;
which means ignore my &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt;, it will become a new folder alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cd public&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git init&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git add .&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git remote add origin &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:git@github.com&#34;&gt;git@github.com&lt;/a&gt;:[your user name]]/[your user name].github.io.git&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git branch -M main&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;git push -u origin main&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;create-the-second-article&#34; &gt;Create the Second Article
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#create-the-second-article&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;hugo new posts/the Second Article.md&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;code&gt;xxx.github.io-creator&lt;/code&gt; (Make sure you are not in &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt; )&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;code posts/the Second Article.md&lt;/code&gt; to edit the file. Make sure not the delete the original content and write in another line to input your content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run &lt;code&gt;hugo -D&lt;/code&gt; to get the new &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter &lt;code&gt;public&lt;/code&gt; for next step
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;git add .&lt;/code&gt; (Don&amp;rsquo;t forget the &lt;code&gt;.&lt;/code&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;git commit -m update&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;git push -f&lt;/code&gt; (Force upload)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wait a few minutes for a second post to appear on your blog!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;upload-pic&#34; &gt;Upload Pic
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#upload-pic&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;method1&#34; &gt;Method1
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#method1&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open the sm.ms website, upload the picture, and get the url of the picture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;![](url) &lt;/code&gt; to show the pic in your article.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;method2&#34; &gt;Method2
&lt;span&gt;
    &lt;a href=&#34;#method2&#34;&gt;
        &lt;svg viewBox=&#34;0 0 28 23&#34; height=&#34;100%&#34; width=&#34;19&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-miterlimit=&#34;10&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Store the image file 1.png in the static directory and get static/1.png&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write &lt;code&gt;![](/1.png)&lt;/code&gt; in the blog Markdown to see the image corresponding to static/1.png&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you want to create an images directory in static, just create it directly, and add &lt;code&gt;/images&lt;/code&gt; in front of the corresponding image, for example
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Put the image file 2.png in the static/images directory to get static/images/2.png&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Just write &lt;code&gt;![](/images/2.png)&lt;/code&gt; in the blog&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you can also Google &amp;ldquo;Hugo insert picture&amp;rdquo; to find the answer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
